nvironment and coordinate with multiple engineering teams across the company to develop and execute flight test plans. </p><p style="min-height:1.5em"></p><p style="min-height:1.5em"><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><p style="min-height:1.5em">In your role as Chief Test Pilot, you will serve as the primary experimental test pilot and coordinate the training and scheduling of all contract pilots. You will ensure that all aspects of experimental flight operations are set up for safety and success. You will coordinate with Reliable’s Part 135 airline operations to support standardization of pilot procedures across the organization and help to develop an aviation safety system.</p><p style="min-height:1.5em"></p><p style="min-height:1.5em"><strong>Basic Success Criteria </strong></p><ul style="min-height:1.5em"><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">FAA Commercial Pilot ASEL with 1500 total flight hours, including at least 500 fixed wing and 500 turbine engine, 500 XC, 100 NT, 75 INST</p></li><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">At least 20 flight hours within the last 12 months in a similar category aircraft to the Caravan</p></li><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">Experience in tactical aircraft or similar operation requiring use of a secondary skillset while piloting</p></li><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">Current Second Class FAA Medical Certificate or higher</p></li><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">8+ years of professional experience in flight operations</p></li><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">2+ years of experience performing or managing a flight test program or in a leadership role within an aviation context</p></li></ul><p style="min-height:1.5em"></p><p style="min-height:1.5em"><strong>Preferred Criteria</strong></p><ul style="min-height:1.5em"><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">Graduate of an SETP recognized flight test school</p></li><li><p style="min-height:1.5em">Bachelor's degree or higher in an engineering or science discipline or equivalent industry experience Caravan 